  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with acute hepatic insult manifesting as jaundice (Sr. Bil. ≥5 mg/dL) and
             coagulopathy (INR≥1.5), complicated within 4 weeks by ascites and/or encephalopathy in
             a patient with previously diagnosed or undiagnosed chronic liver disease.(APASL
             criteria)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  HCC or portal vein thrombosis. Refusal to participate in the study. Sepsis ( Any
             culture positive: blood, urine, focus of infection on Xray chest, any other obvious
             source of infection: UTI, SBP) Multi organ failure. Grade 3 or 4 hepatic
             encephalopathy.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
